									<span class="smalltitle">Live Chat with the Creators of EverQuest</span><br>
									<B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Hey all -- and welcome to today's GameSpy Arcade special event: an exclusive chat with the dev team behind EverQuest: Lost Dungeons of Norrath AND best selling fantasy author, R.A. Salvatore. [GSI]Spiff pauses for thunderous applause<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[PEQ]Muskie&gt;</FONT></B> Shall we begin with Introductions?<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> HI, I'm Bob, and I'm an EQaholic<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hi, I'm Rich Waters - Design Director for EQ. Nice to be here, thanks for coming to the chat.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hello, I'm Shawn Lord - Lead Designer, EverQuest Expansions<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hey, all. :) Scott Hartsman, aka Gallenite, Technical Director, EverQuest. Just here to see Bob talk, really. ;)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Osmith-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hello everyone. I'm Oliver Smith, Lead Designer of EverQuest Live and Legends.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I'm Ryan Barker a game designer on EQLive. Also known as Rytan in game.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rpfister-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hey everyone.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Welcome, gents!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (That'd be Robert Pfister, Producer of EverQuest, and apparently a man of few words...)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (....today)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rpfister-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> ...edited... yes<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> At least the "yes" made it through the chat filter.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Good Job, sir.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Are you guys ready to take some questions -- and give away some games?<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rpfister-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I'd like some games<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> yes please<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Sounds good. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> No questions, just games please.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[PEQ]Muskie&gt;</FONT></B> So Would I!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> To ask a guestion, please type /msg Cobby question and we will post on your behalf (time permitting)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> Please keep your questions limited to LDoN :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rpfister-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Who would vote for Governor of California for? Me or Arnold?<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Mind the typing, he's using his feet.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rpfister-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I can't type, he can't speak.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[PEQ]Muskie&gt;</FONT></B> And I'm Just here to Look good.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Sounds like we've got all the bases covered then :)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Or something.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Anyhow, I know our moderator, the lovely Cobby, has a bazillion questions queued up for you guys<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> if you're ready to start answering.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> By all means.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> Ok - we ready?<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Cool ... one last announcement -- please DO NOT private message our guests during the event<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> leave them in peace!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> your questions will be asked here in the main channel<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> Ok - here we go!<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*IcEmAn{10}* Hey,could you give us some info or just a small hint of what we can expect from the expansion after LDoN?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> It's way too early to talk about that, unfortunately.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> If you could please give me a &lt;d&gt;when you're done , I'll post the next Q<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[PEQ]Muskie&gt;</FONT></B> Translation:"If we told you, we'd have to kill you."<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> At this point, we're focusing all that we have on making sure that LDoN is everything that it can be, while doing the same for our live game. We're really not in a position to talk about what's coming afterward. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hartsman is working on a better answer... and there it is.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Mitri_Deephelm* Will LDoN allow for solo play, or will all content require at least 2 or more in a group?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> The focus of LDoN is definitely on group sized content.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> We'd love to hit all of the different playstyles, but it's not realistic in this case.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Polymer* What are you most proud of as the delvelopers of Lost Dungeons of Norrath</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I think everyone's got something for this one. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I'm excited by the new technologies we've added to the game with this expansion. It will let us do some incredibly immersive and enjoyable content, both for LDoN and the future.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Almost everyone....<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I love the fact that we're doing something that we didn't think would be possible in the existing engine. It's another example of how we can continue to push the game and add new layers of depth to a 5 year old product.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Osmith-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I'd have to say that I'm really impressed with the new technology that is going into LDoN - instanced adventure zones. The team has been working extremely hard to bring high quality content to the players of EverQuest.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> There's new technologies in this expansion? Erm... I should probably duck back over to our office and...uh...check on that.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> ;)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> personally I'm excited about the idea of putting the feel of "dungeon crawling" back into EQ. It's been somethihng that a lot of players have been asking about for a while and it's also something that I enjoyed as a player. Being able to pull together a small group of friends and get something accomplished in an hour or two are some of my most ejoyable times playing EQ or any other game for that matter.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> We're one week into the five week beta process and I'm really happy with how well everything has gone so far.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*ediien* will enchanters be return to thier glorious standing in the new expansion? Like they use be the toons that could take a massive pull and put up the stop sign and controll the crowd.</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Every class will have something to do. The focus is on making sure that everyone feels like they have to be on their toes while they work their way through the dungeons.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hartsman has a cool blue screen, so he'll be back in a bit.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Osmith-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hartsman will be back shortly. Technical issues...<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> A lot of the adventures in LDoN will be challenging situations where a well-played enchanter can make a lot of difference in your group. I think you'll enjoy what's coming up and the role enchanters will continue to play.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Soovu* What is Mr Salvatore's character choice in EQ assuming he plays and it's level</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> From a player's perspective, the dungeons just look great... really great....they're not just boring holes int eh ground, but reall, though-out adventures chambers<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> I've played a bunch of characters....currently working my 51 wizard, Kimmuriel, on Firiona Vie.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Man, fat fingers tonight.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Darkfiend_Eci* Will any of the LDoN Dungeons require certain factions to grant access to them via their NPC's before we can access them?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Sorry, don!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Nope. <BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Glotis* How will the new EQ Lost Dungeons of Norath system work?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Which system, there are several.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> (users cannot reply)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Osmith-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hartsman is on his way in now to discuss some of this.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> We've added instanced zones, there's a new itemization scheme, adventure system, and a new means of modifying items.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (Hi! back.)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> The itemization scheme is one that will allow players to earn credit towards certain items each time that they participate in an adventure.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> This is on top of the rare drops that can be found in the dungeons. These will appear in chests and other objects and on rare npcs.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Also, there will be a means of adding "augmentations" to items.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> The adventure system is pretty exciting to a lot of the people in beta now. You form up a group and then get an adventure goal from the Wayfarer's Brotherhood. This sets you up with a dungeon exclusive to your group, where you can go and have a quick play session. The more adventures you succeed at, the better the Wayfarers lke you, and the better the rewards you can get from them.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> For the adventure system specifically, if you want the best explanation I've seen written up yet, you can check out the Dev Corner at <A href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/" target=_blank>http://eqlive.station.sony.com</A><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> All of the new things we've added this time around are truly letting us get back to the idea of the serious, fun dungeon crawl experience. No matter who you are, 20-65, there's always going to be something for you and a few friends to do.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Sadista* EQ: Will there be more AAs introduced with LDoN?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Yay...my existence has been validated.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Not this time around -- There will still be progression, but more in the sense of improvement via the brand new types of items and now item-Augmentations that can be found in the Lost Dungeons. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Someone kick Ttaylor-SOE please. =)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> lol<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (done)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> No abusing the Marketing guy. ;)<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Legosus_BB_ITSB_Bard* Does Salvatore plan to stay working with EQ developers? and What does Salvatore think of EQ?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Marketing guy, now's your time to shine! =)<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Whew, 21 private conversations will take it out of you, ya know?<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> As far as I know Mister Salvatore has no current "Working" relationship with SOE. He's just a devoted fan like the rest of us. Correct me if I'm wrong, Bob.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> No current working relationship. But yes, I am a huge fan.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*hylonomus* Describe a typical writing session</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> I can't begin to answer here....<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Everytime I type a word, the PM screens start a'popping LOL!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;laughs&gt; That explains it.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> You had us a little curious. ;)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Looks like we're &lt;d&gt;on this one.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> GameSpy meu - options - chat - uncheck the open to change tabs automatically<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Sorry.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> After this question Cobby, I'll ask a EQ Trivia question, to give away a copy of Lost Dungeons of Norrath. Also, please stop PM'ing Mister Salvatore.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Thanks =)<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Okay, that seems to be better....worked this time, I think!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I'll explain how you answer the trivia question when its time. :P<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Can I jump in here for one sec?<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> sure!<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Okay, anyone who has questions can get them to me easily, in two ways. First, my e-mail is rasalvtore @AOL.com (note the missing "A"")<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Second, at my message boards, <A href="http://www.rasalvatore.com/" target=_blank>www.rasalvatore.com</A>, there's an interactive thread set up where I answer questions.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Now I have no idea of how to answer the Direct Tells coming, in, but hey, I am reading them!<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Hehe, &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> Trivia Time! :)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> rock!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Nevada!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I know all of these!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[PEQ]Muskie&gt;</FONT></B> Area 51!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Allrighty...the first person to PM the anser to this question to Spiff, wins a copy of LDoN.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I'm ready!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Employees are not valid winners :P<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> You'll need to type /msg [GSI]Spiff with your answers<BR