_Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Then I get what's called "gallies" (typeset product), where I can make only small changes.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*TzeeTzeetop* question to RAS : Do you feel its more artistic desire or commercial success that drives you to continue with your Forgotten Realms Novels?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> It's both, to tell the truth. People want those books - o boy, do they!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (While we're holding on the answer, Cobby, could you please re-flag osmith-soe? Thanks. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> And I love writing Drizzt and the gang.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Next Trivia Question: "After a battle that left him mortally wounded, this king was "rebuilt" to become a clockwork cyborg who has ruled for centuries. Send a tell to [GSI]Spiff with the answer to win a copy of Lost Dungeons of Norrath!<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Also, WotC's giving me pretty much complete control over what I do, so it's not like they're tying my hands in any way.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Whoops..sorry thought you were done :)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Greiver got it<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> stop<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> dang that was fast<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> I've come to understand that, no matter what else I do, even killing Chewie, I'm going to be known for Drizzt. That's very cool with me.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> answer was King Ak'Kanon<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> lots of right answers<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Griever was mr speedy<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> lots of fans :)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> ok ready for a couple more Q's?<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Yep<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Kendricke* Within Lost Dungeons of Norrath, it has been stated that a new item feature will allow special items which can augment the abilities of already existing items (ala Diablo 2?). Can you elaborate upon this system a bit more? Will the augmentation be permanant? What restrictions will be placed on the augmentation (as a general rule)?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Gladly. These augmentations, unlike previous modifications to items (dyes), will both be permanent and attached to the item, as opposed to being attached to the slot that the item contains.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> A subtle difference, for sure, but one that's meant a gigantic pile of work as most of EverQuest's item system has had to be rewritten in the past months.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> In the end, we'll end up with a much better system that will hopefully, some day, allow for all different kinds of customizations.<BR>[PEQ]Muskie remembers screaming in horror the first time he Saw a Rainbow-colored Barbarian.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> As for the restrictions, there are going to be specific types of augmentations. Some equipment in the game may be able to accept one or more different types of augmentations, as we described a little bit the other day on our web site. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Muskie, that's what happens when you go on blind dates.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> *Polymer* Are there new disciplines for non casters coming out with LDoN?<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (Rich is grabbing this one...)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> New features that cover class balance (like disciplines) are the kind of things we try not to tie to expansions. We definitely feel that disciplines need some updates and improvements, and it's something we'll be doing as a free live update instead of expecting you to buy a box to balance your class.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*leyor* I have a question for the LDON developers please:) "Seeing as LDoN consists of one group encounters, how do you plan on balancing it? As a group of high end players in plane of time gear will enjoy a vast advantage over more casual players. Which player will the content be geared towards"?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> We're balancing it with both in mind.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Also, players have the ability to pick harder adventure types.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*theron420* question for Salvatore, What do you think about the differences and similarities between the ranger class and what you invisioned for a ranger when you wrote the dark elf series, would you like anything changed about the class in EQ?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> oops!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> sorry :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> No worries =)<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></FONT></B> I'll wait for the &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Also, with the new technology we've added with LDoN, all 48 of the zones in the expansion will work for anyone between levels 20 and 65.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> so, if you're level 32, you get 48 zones. If you're level 65 you get 48 zones.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> You can play in all of them, and they all have level appropriate content for you and your group.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> done<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[PEQ]Muskie&gt;</FONT></B> <B>What about Equipment? a level 20 decked in full rubicite might throw off the balance with a level 20 in Fine Steel.</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> The Adventure system in general also has a setting that lets people who are slightly better off than others specifically request, "Hey, give me a harder adventure."<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> That level 20, assuming he's in a group of his peers, would very likely find a much better experience (and suitable reward) by selecting a more difficult adventure. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> Trivia Time!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> w00t!<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Ranger is hardly my invention. Obviously, my ranger isn't as magically inclined as the EQ one (and actually, if Drizzt were to be an EQ character, I'd think of him more as a straight fighter. &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> So there! &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Okay, as long \\\\as we don't miss out on Bob's answer - I'd like to hear it too :)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> no worries.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> <B>Another Trivia question..."Don't lose sight of the Leatherfoot Deputy, who can be seen swimming from the windows of this tavern.</B><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Morgrist got it<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1