in character levels on the team. There's many that do have a high level character as their main, but also a lot in the low to mid levels. We've got a large team, it covers a lot of different viewpoints and experiences.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Since I've never gotten above 51, I have yet to experience the real high-end game, but so far, I think the best levels are 15-35.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> *Morgrist* Question: Being one of Niami's little minions, the teaser bits on tradeskills from R. Hills have been interesting. Would you expand on what we'll be seeing with tradeskills and LDoN,and will it include the "customizable" item bits mentioned this week?<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> It would explain all of the details in this forum. We are always concentrating on expanding tradeskills. We know that people enjoy them, so they'll always be considered when making an expansion or adding other content to the game.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Errr.. add the word hard in there somewhere.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I think that's a &lt;d&gt;for now.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*hal9000* For Rick Waters: can you explain more about the gem slots? will their be recipes similar to Diablo II?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> They're wrestling over the keyboard. Someone will answer you shortly.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (Shawn and Jake will be humming elevator music in the background while we wait.)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (Jake will be making threatening gestures in my general direction.)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> It's similiar in that it allows you to upgrade a piece of equipment by combining items with it, but the new system is much more customizable in terms of what kinds of attributes you can adorn your equipment with.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> BTW, I'm not rich, but I'm answering &gt;:)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Wait! More specifics are on the way!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Specifically there's types of armor that will only accept certain types of upgrades<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> ("armor" == "equipment.")<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> so you might be able to put adornment A on a certain piece of equipment, but not on a different piece of equipment.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> You'll also be able to remove the adornment from the equipment, but it will then be lost forever.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> So you'll want to be careful with which adornments you want to use, and on which items.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I think that's about as much info as I can give without going into nitty gritty specifics.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> so &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Mad_Man* Will a group of two be able to enjoy LDON or will it require a full group to see the new zones?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> answering coming from Rich.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> The plan currently is to require groups of 4 or more. We'll likely provide future adventures for smaller groups, but when we roll this out we want to be able to have as many people using it as possible. As Hartsman said, we're expecting to be able to run 11,000 instances when it launches so if we require group sizes of 4 or more, we'll service at least 44k people.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> In the long run though, we all hope to make these adventures available for all players, regardless of group size.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> One thing that we're noticing on the Beta server is that even those who generally aren't fond of grouping are finding it much easier to get into groups, now that there are central meeting places to hook up with others. That, and the /LFG tool is really coming in handy, and being used quite a bit. I suspect that even the ultra-casual will be able to hop in, find some people to group with, then get going without waiting long.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d again&gt; :)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Iniarini* I would like to know if Mr. Salvatore has a website listing all his work. :) Thank you.</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> My (official) website, <A href="http://www.rasalvatore.com/" target=_blank>www.rasalvatore.com</A> (I sound like an ad campaign!) list all the books, lists signing tours and has a great message board gang.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Also, we do e-signings, where you buy the books through the website and get them personally signed. It's pretty cool because people can order a book, say, for a friend that would be inscribed, "To Joe, Merry Christmas! Spend it with Drizzt! R.A. Salvatore"<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>Twofer: *Khan8156* Will there be anymore tales involving Danica and Cadderly? and *Raivan* Will we see more books that continue the adventures of Artemis and Jarlaxle?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> I intend to go back to Artemis and Jarlaxle as soon as I'm done the HUnter's Blades series. As for Cadderly and Danica, I hope to find ways to weave them in. I'm also thinking that a Jarlaxle/Zaknafein story set way in the past might be fun.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> *Glotis* What new engine are you using to recreate the old school dungeon andventuring?<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Hmm..<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Shawn answering...<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;sorry<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> This really isn't a matter of a new engine. It's taking the existing core of EQ, diving into some of the scariest, oldest, parts of it. Surgically removing them, and replacing them with brand new systems that do all of the things that we need them to do.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> It's less a product of the engine and more a matter of placing people in complex dungeon environments. Each dungeon is roughly 3/4 the size of the ones you can find in Norrath at the moment. All of them have traps, objects to interact with (chests, barrels, etc), and plenty of monsters.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (Translating my above answer after Rich mentioned me that he doesn't know what I said -- Essentially, it's all our game engine, still. We just ripped out lots of old stuff, and replaced it with some new stuff that rivals any 3rd gen game out there, as far as the instancing is concerned. And with that, I'll let Shawn say things that make even more sense. :))<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*zakupilot256* i got a good question, Who is Drizzt ?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> rofl<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> :)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> :P<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> He was laughing at me, zakupilot.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> ...and he won't stop.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;nods&gt;Sorry, Zak - Was laughing at shawn's...er...brief, continuation. And he's right -- I'm not. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Drizzt is....hmm, how do I answer that?<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> He's the guy who started the dark elf craze, I think. Which has people loving me and hating me, depending on whether or not all their gamers want to play a twin-scimitar-wielding dark elf ranger with a 600 pound cat friend.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> *Iceblast* Is there a chance that when you try to Augmentation a item that you make it worse, rather then better?<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> When you examine the augmentations, you'll be able to check out all of their stats, as if they were their own standalone iteme.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Or "items," if I could type.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Augmentations can have both positives and negatives, so you may be able to attach an augmentation that has +10 strength and -10 agility if you wanted to. You'll be able to see what you're getting before you decide to use it.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> It's really not a matter of, "Surprise! It's got -10000 HP, and you're in a death loop!" ;)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;D!&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Vashan* For Mr Salvatore Have you ever written under a Pen name?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Nope. But I have a book that I want to write which, if published, will come out under a different name. I don't want anyone reading it with preconceived notions! &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> *Jureld* If you have time please question for RAS "Do you forsee any of your novels becoming movies?"<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I'd cast Chris Rock as Drizzt!<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> I hope so. There's certainly been a lot of interest for both Drizzt and DemonWars. I think that Peter Jackson's excellent work has opened the doors for fantasy movies that don't make fun of fantasy - I jjust hope they stay open.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Keep your fingers crossed. Mine certainly are! &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> *sweets_eq* what kind of new quests will be given in the new dungeons... will there be more interesthing,fun,or hard ones???<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> "Yes!"<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I think all three of those things are important.. so if the question was "which of those are we focusing on?" then we're trying to hit all of those qualities. If the question was "Will any of your quests be interesting, hard, or fun?" ... I hope so ;)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> There will be several different adventure types. Everything from saving a hostage or assassinating the dungeon's boss, to wiping the whole place out.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*QuintenWolfe* GameSpy folks, since this event is going on here, is there going to be any future games/ventures with SOE and Gamespy to allow us EQ players this type of interaction in EQ?? this is a good system.</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> And the settings around those quests are simply beautiful, I can attest!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Is that marketing guy still here?<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin][GSI]Spiff&gt;</FONT></B> Uh ... we sure hope so!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1