 showing for this chat is any indication, of course we'd be looking to do something like this again with the fine folks at GameSpy. (Sorry for the long response time.)<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> Forgiven :)<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*Neatton* Is there going to be a large all consuming quest to LDoN that ties together the expansion like there was in PoP?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> As you play through LDoN, you'll notice that the storyline answers some of the existing questions and builds the basis for many of the expansions to come.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Many....expansions....to....come - Oh god, I gotta write more books.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> There isn't a long quest, like the one seen in PoP, but we will be delivering lore to you as you play through the expansion.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> <B></B>&lt;laughs&gt; <BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> d<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*rhholmes* How did some of the developers here learn their skills? i.e. How did they become programmers?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Last 3 questions after this one, then I'll do a bunch of trivia questions and give away 7 more LDON copies and 10 copies of EverQuest Evolutions.<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> (After our wonderful guests have said their goodbyes of course.)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I actually started out writing content for a commercial MUD called "Scepter" when I was 15. Decided I wanted to be able to know how to make an entire online game, and that was pretty much the end of the road for my chances of a normal career. It's been online games ever since. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I started as a QA tester 11 years ago for Sierra Online's Shadow of Yserbius game. I worked hard and learned from the people around me, and managed to move into a game design position. Since then, I've been lucky enough to meet a lot of incredible game developers and learn a lot from them.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I took a lot of chemistry class, heh. Seriously I just grew up playing games, and messing with computurs. I took a number of Computer Science classes in college, but the most important thing is to have a love for what you're doing and the drive to make it happen.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Osmith-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I was really interested in the gaming industry and decided to focus my studies on tools that are available within it (sql, vb, c++, etc.). I also spent a lot of time working with standard office tools (word, excel, etc.) and kept learning what I could. I got my foot into the door by becoming a Technical Support Rep for VI/SOE back in 1999.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> It started with picking up some random fantasy novels. You know, something about a dwarf, barbarian, a guy and his cat... that sort of thing. It eventually evolved into me spending plenty of time playing Pen and Paper games and then every video game I could get my hands on. But then again, I work in design, not programming.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*LordTithus* For the devs: How will corpse retrievals work with instanced dungeons? Will we see more of the graveyard mechanic?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Kind of.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Since these instanced zones are launched for your group on demand, if you fail an adventure and are unable to complete it in its time limit, your corpse is automatically returned, at that point, to the place where you originally zoned in.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> However, it's not fully-automatic in the same sense as GY's are.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> A goblin will sell your corpse to the nearest vendor for 2pp. G'luck getting it back!<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Ack... sorry. Scott, stop hitting me.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> LOL<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> hey, my &lt;laughs&gt; got spam-snipped.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;mutter&gt; <BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Corpse? You mean characters DIE in EQ? Wow.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Serious!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> The gnomes do if you punt them far enough...erm...nevermind...<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Anyway, don't be surprised to see corpses being spit out of dungeon entrances across Norrath. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Some people don't play so well, I guess.....<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> a_rujarkian_entrance00 says, "...and STAY OUT!"<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>QuintenWolfe* Are there any plans to add more animations, model graphics and SOE sponsored Roleplaying Events? Like the Historic ones?</B><BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Next question is the last one...pick a good one, Cobby. :) (Thanks for the fabulous moderating job by the way Cobby &amp; Spiff.)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> At the moment, we do have some folks looking into what kinds of improvements we can get away with making to EQ's graphics engine without completely traumatizing the average system -- That's part of the reason we're now asking people to submit their system info on log in. We're actually using that information for good, not evil. We're trying to find ways to improve EQ that don't break what's gone before. :)<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> We're going to be adding more live events for people to take part in. We haven't had a big one since the fall of Grobb, which went over very well with players, but we do hope to get another couple of major events in soon.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;done&gt; <BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> I saved this one for last :)<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admin]Cobby&gt;</FONT></B> <B>*sweets_eq* (for RAS) on an average ...how many cups of coffee do you drink when writing a novel???</B><BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Haha! Depends on how many battle scenes I have to write!<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I think the real question is who drinks more, Salvatore on a novel or the Dev Team on an expansion?<BR><B><FONT color=#c1d3ff>&lt;Ttaylor-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> Coffee, thati s.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;SLord-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> ...<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Hartsman-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> US...! oh nm<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rbarker-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I dont' drink coffee, it's all mountain dew.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> When I offed the Wookie....well, let's just say it wasn't pretty round the coffee maker.<BR><B><FONT color=#fffbc1>&lt;Rwaters-SOE&gt;</FONT></B> I avoid the coffee.. stunts your growth.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> Developer team drinks more, without doubt. My boss let's me go to bed.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> lets me....duh<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> I need coffee.<BR><B><FONT color=#ffd7d8>&lt;R_A__Salvatore&gt;</FONT></B> &lt;d&gt;<BR><B><FONT color=#c1ffc1>&lt;[Admi